  "prompt": "Does my H1B visa transfer impact my spouse's H4 visa?",
  "response": "The process of transferring an H-1B visa generally does not directly affect your spouse's H-4 visa status. Here are key points to consider:\n\n1. **H-4 Visa Dependence**: The H-4 visa for your spouse is linked to your H-1B visa status. As long as you maintain valid H-1B status, your spouse can continue to hold the H-4 status.\n\n2. **H-1B Transfer Implications**: When you transfer your H-1B to a new employer, it involves filing a new H-1B petition with USCIS. This process typically involves the new employer submitting a change of employer petition (also known as H-1B portability).\n\n3. **Validity Continuation**: Your spouse\u2019s H-4 status remains valid as long as your H-1B status is maintained, and the new H-1B petition is approved. It\u2019s important to ensure that the transfer application is properly filed and approved.\n\n4. **H-4 Visa Extensions**: If the change in your employment alters the dates or validity of your H-1B visa, it might be a good idea to file for an extension or amendment for your spouse's H-4 status to align with the new H-1B approval.\n\n5. **Travel Considerations**: If your spouse plans to travel outside the U.S. during your H-1B transfer, make sure to consult with an immigration attorney to ensure smooth re-entry.\n\nAlways consult directly with an immigration attorney to handle any specific details of your case and ensure compliance with all immigration laws and procedures.",
